---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service for whyismywebsiteslow.com."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</p>

    <div class="prose prose-invert mt-8 max-w-none prose-p:text-slate-300 prose-li:text-slate-300 prose-headings:text-slate-100 prose-strong:text-slate-100">
      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the whyismywebsiteslow.com website, products, and services
        (the "Service"). By using the Service, you agree to these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Accounts and eligibility</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You must provide accurate information when creating an account.</li>
        <li>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account and credentials.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Do not misuse the Service, attempt to break security, or interfere with others’ use.</li>
        <li>Do not use the Service to scan or analyze systems you do not own or have permission to test.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Payments</h2>
      <p>
        Certain features may be offered for a fee (for example, one-time report unlocks, subscriptions, or services).
        Prices and billing terms are presented at checkout.
      </p>

      <h2>Service availability</h2>
      <p>
        We may modify, suspend, or discontinue parts of the Service at any time. We do not guarantee uninterrupted
        availability.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        The Service is provided "as is" and "as available". Performance metrics and recommendations are informational
        and may vary based on third-party data sources, site changes, and network conditions.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
        punitive damages, or any loss of profits, revenue, data, or goodwill, arising from your use of the Service.
      </p>

      <h2>Termination</h2>
      <p>
        You may stop using the Service at any time. We may suspend or terminate access if we reasonably believe you
        violated these Terms or used the Service in a way that could cause harm.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to these Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. If we make material changes, we will post the updated Terms on this
        page.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For billing questions, the fastest option is to reply to the receipt email sent after checkout. For other
        questions, use the site navigation to find the appropriate page and we’ll route your message.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

